Key Match Events: The Astros worked eight no-hit innings before turning it over to Ryan Pressly in the ninth.
Ryan Noda's ninth-inning single broke the no-hit bid.
Seth Brown followed Noda's hit with an RBI single.
Paul Blackburn started the game with a three-inning performance.
Easton Lucas struck out Yordan Alvarez but allowed a solo home run to Kyle Tucker.
Post-Match Reflections: Seth Brown commented on helping Ryan Noda with information about Ryan Pressly.
Easton Lucas reflected on his performance, noting he could learn from the experience.
